{"pageProps":{"id":"sicp2.1.1","title":"SISP 2.1.1: Rational numbers","date":"2020-07-08","tags":["SICP"],"content":"<h2>Exercise 2.1</h2>\n<p>Here is how you construct rational number:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"hljs language-scheme\">(<span class=\"hljs-name\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\">define</span></span> (<span class=\"hljs-name\">make-rat</span> n d)\n  (<span class=\"hljs-name\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\">let</span></span> ((<span class=\"hljs-name\">g</span> (<span class=\"hljs-name\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\">gcd</span></span> n d))\n       (<span class=\"hljs-name\">sign</span> (<span class=\"hljs-name\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\">if</span></span> (<span class=\"hljs-name\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\">&#x3C;</span></span> d <span class=\"hljs-number\">0</span>) <span class=\"hljs-number\">-1</span> <span class=\"hljs-number\">1</span>)))\n    (<span class=\"hljs-name\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\">cons</span></span> (<span class=\"hljs-name\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\">/</span></span> n g sign) (<span class=\"hljs-name\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\">/</span></span> d g sign))))\n\n(<span class=\"hljs-name\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\">define</span></span> numer car)\n(<span class=\"hljs-name\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\">define</span></span> denom cdr)\n\n(<span class=\"hljs-name\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\">define</span></span> (<span class=\"hljs-name\">print-rat</span> x)\n  (<span class=\"hljs-name\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\">newline</span></span>)\n  (<span class=\"hljs-name\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\">display</span></span> (<span class=\"hljs-name\">numer</span> x))\n  (<span class=\"hljs-name\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\">display</span></span> <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"/\"</span>)\n  (<span class=\"hljs-name\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\">display</span></span> (<span class=\"hljs-name\">denom</span> x)))</code></pre>\n<p>That's it, change sign of both parts when denominator is negative, you could do that by multiplying or dividing by -1.</p>"},"__N_SSG":true}